Subject: So this is your first Penguicon...
Description: So it's your first time! One of us! One of us! Great, now that you're here, how do you do it right? What's up with the ribbons? How do you pick what you want do when soooomg many things are going on? Where's the free beer? What happened to the brazilian beef? Why is hand sanitizer terrible salad dressing? Learn some survival tips and hear some heart-warming stories from some seasoned experts, previous conchairs, and convention organizers!  Speakers include:Cassy Sinke, Janet Gocay, Scott Kennedy, Nuri Gocay, Jessica Roland - Track: Penguicon  - Duration: 1 hour

Subject: How to Work with People on the Spectrum: A Brief Discussion About Autism
Description: Did you ever wonder or even know that 95% of autistic people (ASD) are unemployed or underemployed? This panel will inform you of the misinformation surrounding autism and how we can help autistic people after high school or even college. Be yourself and not somebody else.  Speakers include:Ian Sterrett, Greg Walters, Tammy Morris, Nuri Gocay - Track: Life  - Duration: 1 hour
